casebody.data:
Kate A. McLAUGHLIN et al. v. CAPITAL COMPANY. No. 10064. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 2, 1942. Anthony & Rogers, of San Francisco, Cal., and James A. Walker, of Salinas, Cal., for appellants. J. Benton Tulley and Keyes & Erskine, all of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before GARRECHT, HANEY, and HEALY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of the motion of ap-pellee, and good cause therefor appearing, ordered appeal herein dismissed for failure of appellants to take appeal within statutory time, that a decree be filed and entered accordingly, and that mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
